---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ElementCard from '../../components/ElementCard.astro';
import CloudDivider from '../../components/CloudDivider.astro';
import { elements } from '../../data/elements';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Five Elements — Wood, Fire, Earth, Metal, Water | Wu Xing Wellness"
  description="A plain-English guide to the Chinese five elements and how each connects an organ, season, flavor, color and emotion."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Wu Xing · 五行</span>
        <h2>Meet the Five Elements</h2>
        <p>
          In traditional Chinese thought, everything is made of five moving energies. Each governs a part of the
          body and a thread of the mind — and each has foods and seasons that keep it in flow.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="element-grid">
        {elements.map((e) => <ElementCard element={e} />)}
      </div>
      <CloudDivider />
      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:30px">
        <p>
          The five elements are not rigid labels but a way to notice balance. Too much Fire and you burn out;
          too little Wood and plans stall. The goal of traditional self-care is simply to keep all five in
          gentle motion — through food, season, rest and attention.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
